<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,698,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
Annual, procumbent undershrubs, 
<quantity box="[588,703,734,760]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="cm" value="35.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="30.0">30–40 cm</quantity>
high. Stem branched, angular, sparsely glandular hairy, winged; wings 
<quantity box="[211,305,769,795]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
wide, denticulate. Leaves aromatic, alternate, sessile; lamina lanceolate, 
<quantity box="[1132,1216,769,795]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 cm</quantity>
long and up to 
<quantity box="[1395,1451,769,795]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
wide, sparsely glandular-punctate dorsiventrally; leaf-base decurrent, forming cauline wings, margin denticulate, apex mucronate-apiculate. Inflorescence compound capitulum; numerous heterogamous capitula (partial heads) born on a conical, hollow receptacle of the compound head. Compound heads purple, ovoid-conical, 
<quantity box="[1172,1228,875,901]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
or less in length as well as width, pedunculated, leaf-opposed; peduncles 
<quantity box="[743,826,910,936]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 cm</quantity>
long, winged. Common involucre bracts 7–8, biseriate, c. 
<quantity box="[161,253,945,972]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
long, ovate to oblong, hairy, ciliate, scarious along the margin, apiculate with 
<quantity box="[1115,1228,945,972]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
protracted tip. Each capitulum sessile; comprised of 4 bracts, 2 centrally located bisexual florets surrounded by 4 outer, female florets, both without pappus. Of the 4 bracts, the involucre bract similar to that of the compound head; the other 3 bracts membranous with truncate, ciliated apex, c. 
<quantity box="[486,555,1051,1077]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
; of the three, 2 laterally folded, boat-shaped; 1 adaxial, broad at apex, tapering towards base. Female florets 
<quantity box="[464,557,1086,1112]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long; corolla tube filiform, translucent, creamy-white, glanduliferous, minutely 3 lobed; lobes pink; ovary cylindrical, hairy, pale yellow; stigma bifid, dark pink. Bisexual florets c. 
<quantity box="[1291,1386,1121,1148]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
long, corolla tube cylindrical, 5-lobed at apex, constricted near the base and below the lobes, lobes pink; constricted region, lobes, and ovary glanduliferous; glands sessile. Stamens 5, syngenesious, anthers sagittate, dorsifixed; ovary oblong, sparsely hairy, style dark pink, covered entirely with sweeping hair, slightly bifid at apex. Achenes of female flowers cylindrical, hairy, c. 
<quantity box="[366,434,1262,1288]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; those of bisexual flowers obovoid, glabrous, 
<quantity box="[949,1087,1261,1288]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<figureCitation box="[1098,1174,1262,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,206,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-19@1.[177,1410,206,1884]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Analytical photographs of Sphaeranthus gomphrenoides. A. Habit; B. Twigs bearing compound capitulum; C. Compound head; D. Vertical section of a compound head; E, F. Involucre bracts of a compound head (E) and a capitulum (F) (left—abaxial view, right—adaxial view); G. Single capitulum comprising three bracts, female and bisexual flowers; H. Adaxial and lateral bracts of a capitulum; I. Female flower with exserted bifid stigma; J. Bisexual flowers (left—younger, right—older with anthers exserted from corolla tube); K, L. Achenes of female (K) and bisexual (L) flowers." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316636/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1228,1245,1262,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[167,1400,204,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,187,1795]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Line drawing of Sphaeranthus gomphrenoides. A. Flowering twig; B. Compound head; C. Vertical section of a compound head showing hollow conical receptacle; D. Involucre bract of a compound head; E. Single capitulum with 3 bracts and 4 female, 2 bisexual flowers; F. Involucre bract of a capitulum; G. Adaxial and lateral bracts of a capitulum; H. Female flower; I, J. Bisexual flowers at younger (I) and older (J) stage with anthers exserted from corolla tube; K, L.Achenes of bisexual (K) and female (L) flowers. Illustrated by Oshin based on VVN 649." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316640/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">2</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
